{:itonami.blueprint/id "cloud-itonami-isic-3250"
 :itonami.blueprint/name "Manufacture of medical and dental instruments and supplies"
 :itonami.blueprint/isic-rev5 "3250"
 :itonami.blueprint/domain :medical-dental-instrument/manufacturing
 :itonami.blueprint/license "AGPL-3.0-or-later"
 :itonami.blueprint/social-impact [:patient-safety :worker-safety :materials-safety]
 :itonami.blueprint/governor :medical-instrument-plant-operations-governor
 :itonami.blueprint/robotics true
 :itonami.blueprint/required-technologies [:robotics :identity :forms :dmn :bpmn :audit-ledger :cae]
 :itonami.blueprint/status :public-oss
 :itonami.blueprint/maturity :implemented
 :itonami.blueprint/implemented-slice
 "MedInstrAdvisor ⊣ Medical Instrument Plant Operations Governor,
 langgraph-clj StateGraph, append-only audit ledger. A plant OPERATIONS
 COORDINATION actor for medical and dental instrument and supplies
 manufacturing (precision machining/molding/sterilization-validation
 lines producing surgical/dental instruments and supplies) -- not
 direct machining/molding/sterilization-line-equipment control
 authority and not FDA 510(k)/CE-mark regulatory-clearance authority.
 Four ops (`:log-production-batch` / `:schedule-maintenance` /
 `:flag-safety-concern` / `:coordinate-shipment`), all `:effect
 :propose` only. Twelve concrete governor checks elaborate this
 blueprint's four HARD invariants: propose-only effect, closed op
 allowlist, closed proposal-effect allowlist (no direct machining/
 molding/sterilization-line-equipment control), permanent equipment-
 actuate block, permanent regulatory-clearance-authority block (this
 actor never self-issues an FDA 510(k)/CE-mark regulatory clearance),
 independent equipment verification/registration before maintenance
 scheduling, independent batch verification/registration before
 shipment coordination, independent shipment-quantity recompute
 against the batch's own logged production quantity, double-schedule
 guard, device-class validation, sterility-assurance-level plausibility
 validation, and nonconformance-rate plausibility validation.
 Safety-concern flagging (sterility-validation-failure/materials-
 biocompatibility/device-defect) ALWAYS escalates to a human plant
 supervisor; `:log-production-batch` is the only op eligible to
 auto-commit, and only at phase 3 when governor-clean."}
